《'''梦蛇'''》（{{lang-en|''Dreamsnake''}}）是美国作家[[冯达·麦金泰尔|冯达·麦金泰尔]]1978年的[[科學幻想|科幻]]小说，由她1973年首获[[星云奖|星云奖]]的短篇小说《[[雾草沙|雾草沙]]》扩充而成<ref name="Ashley-2007">{{cite book | first = Mike | last = Ashley | title = Gateways to Forever: The Story of the Science-Fiction Magazines from 1970 to 1980 | pages = 23–26 | url = https://books.google.co.jp/books?id=2qkmF8HvP_gC&redir_esc=y | year = 2007 | publisher = Liverpool University Press | isbn = 978-1-84631-003-4 | access-date = 2021-03-23}}</ref><ref name="Loc74">{{cite web | url = http://www.sfadb.com/Nebula_Awards_1974 | title = Nebula Awards 1974 | work = Science Fiction Awards Database | publisher = Locus | access-date = 2021-03-23 | archive-date = 2020-11-02 | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201102180718/http://www.sfadb.com/Nebula_Awards_1974}}</ref>。故事发生在[[核浩劫|核浩劫]]后的地球，主人翁叫舞蛇，能用[[基因工程|转基因]]蛇治病，书名“梦蛇”是舞蛇用于治病的外星蛇，毒液能让人在临死前进入美妙梦境。小说情节主线是舞蛇在梦蛇死亡后寻找替代品。

《梦蛇》是科幻文学[[第二波女性主義|第二波女权主义]]的典范之作，作者笔下的英雄征程以女子为核心，颠覆传统文艺作品的性别定势，还通过避免[[第三人稱|性别代词]]等手段挑战读者对角色的[[性別認同|性別認同]]。小说从女权立场探讨各种社会结构和性别固定思维，检视治疗与跨文化互动主题。

小说面世后广受好评，获1978年[[星雲獎最佳長篇小說獎|星雲獎最佳長篇小說獎]]，1979年[[雨果獎最佳長篇小說|雨果獎最佳長篇小說]]和[[轨迹奖最佳长篇小说|轨迹奖最佳长篇小说]]。评论关注主角舞蛇的实力，称赞作者文笔和小说主题。学者黛安·伍德声称《梦蛇》体现“科幻文学以语言和文化规范实验产生美感的潜力”<ref name="Wood-1990">{{cite journal | last = Wood | first = Diane S. | title = Breaking the Code: Vonda N. McIntyre's Dreamsnake | journal = Extrapolation | volume = 31 | issue = 1 | year = 1990 | pages = 63–72 | issn = 0014-5483 | doi = 10.3828/extr.1990.31.1.63}}</ref>{{rp|63}}；[[娥蘇拉·勒瑰恩|娥蘇拉·勒瑰恩]]称赞小说“如山上溪流般迅速、干净、清晰、美丽，令人兴奋不已”<ref name="Le Guin 1978">{{cite journal | title = Dreamsnake | journal = The Magazine of Fantasy and Science Fiction | year = 1978 | volume = 54 | issue = 4–6 | page = 31 | url = https://books.google.co.jp/books?id=g5m0AAAAIAAJ&redir_esc=y}}导言引述勒瑰恩的评论</ref>。

== 背景 ==
1971年，住在[[西雅圖|西雅圖]]的[[冯达·麦金泰尔|冯达·麦金泰尔]]（{{lang|en|Vonda N. McIntyre}}）创办[[号角西作家工作坊|号角西作家工作坊]]并协助运作到1973年，[[娥蘇拉·勒瑰恩|娥蘇拉·勒瑰恩]]是工作坊讲师<ref name="Holland">{{cite news | last = Holland | first = Steve | title = Vonda N McIntyre obituary | url = https://www.theguardian.com/books/2019/apr/04/vonda-mcintyre-obituary | access-date = 2021-03-23 | work = The Guardian | date = 2019-04-04 | archive-date = 2020-11-07 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201107234951/https://www.theguardian.com/books/2019/apr/04/vonda-mcintyre-obituary | dead-url = no }}</ref>。1972年工作坊开课期间布署的写作任务是随机选择两个词为题创作，一个是精神类辞汇，另一个是技术类。麦金泰尔的作品发展成1973年短篇小说《雾草沙》（{{lang|en|Of Mist, and Grass, and Sand}}），后来进一步扩张成《梦蛇》，第一章与《雾草沙》内容相同<ref name="Holland" />。麦金泰尔1978年作品《破碎圆顶》（{{lang|en|The Broken Dome}}）和《蛇之死》（{{lang|en|The Serpent's Death}}）均包含《梦蛇》部分段落<ref name="PhilSP">{{cite web | last = Stephenson-Payne | first = Phil | title = Stories, Listed by Author | url = http://www.philsp.com/homeville/ISFAC/s207.htm#A3167 | website = Index to Science Fiction Anthologies and Collections | access-date = 2021-03-23 | archive-date = 2021-01-25 | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210125021452/http://www.philsp.com/homeville/isfac/s207.htm#A3167 }}</ref>，因此《梦蛇》是在多部短篇小说基础上扩充而成的长篇<ref>{{cite encyclopedia | first1 = David | last1 = Langford | first2 = Peter | last2 = Nicholls | first3 = Cheryl | last3 = Morgan | title = Hugo | encyclopedia = The Encyclopedia of Science Fiction | date = 2020-09-20 | url = http://www.sf-encyclopedia.com/entry/hugo | editor-last1 = Nicholls | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210310154302/http://www.sf-encyclopedia.com/entry/hugo | editor-first1 = Peter | editor-last2 = Clute | editor-first2 = John | editor-last3 = Sleight | editor-first3 = Graham | publisher = Gollancz | access-date = 2021-03-23 | archive-date = 2021-03-10 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

《梦蛇》是麦金泰尔第二部长篇小说，1978年霍顿·米夫林出版社（{{lang|en|Houghton Mifflin}}）发行，斯蒂芬·亚历山大（{{lang|en|Stephen Alexander}}）绘制封面<ref name="ESF">{{cite encyclopedia | title = McIntyre, Vonda N. | first = John | last = Clute | encyclopedia = The Encyclopedia of Science Fiction | date = 2020-04-13 | url = http://sf-encyclopedia.com/entry/mcintyre_vonda_n | editor-last1 = Nicholls | editor-first1 = Peter | editor-last2 = Clute | editor-first2 = John | editor-last3 = Sleight | editor-first3 = Graham | publisher = Gollancz | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210126055258/http://www.sf-encyclopedia.com/entry/mcintyre_vonda_n | access-date = 2021-03-23 | archive-date = 2021-01-26 }}</ref><ref name="Lefanu-1989">{{cite book | first = Sarah | last = Lefanu | title = Feminism and Science Fiction | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=at4bAQAAIAAJ | year = 1989 | publisher = Indiana University Press | isbn = 978-0-253-33287-5 | pages = 90–91 | access-date = 2021-03-23 | archive-date = 2021-10-14 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20211014090838/https://books.google.com/books?id=at4bAQAAIAAJ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。故事发生在[[核浩劫|核浩劫]]后的地球，“所有知道或在乎（核浩劫）原因的人”无一幸存<ref name="Holland" /><ref name="Sandomir">{{cite news | last = Sandomir | first = Richard | title = Vonda N. McIntyre, 70, Champion of Women in Science Fiction, Dies | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/05/obituaries/vonda-n-mcintyre-dead.html | access-date = 2021-03-23 | work = The New York Times | date = 2019-04-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201108000653/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/05/obituaries/vonda-n-mcintyre-dead.html | archive-date = 2020-11-08 | dead-url = no }}</ref>，大部分动物灭绝，地球上众多区域充满辐射，漫天的尘土如黑云遮天<ref name="Paulsen-1984">{{cite journal | first = Inge-Lise | last = Paulsen | title = Can Women Fly?: Vonda McIntyre's ''Dreamsnake'' and Sally Gearhart's ''The Wanderground'' | journal = Women's Studies International Forum | volume = 7 | issue = 2 | year = 1984 | pages = 104–106 | doi = 10.1016/0277-5395(84)90064-5}}</ref>{{rp|104}}。人类社会虽然存在，但据新闻工作者山姆·乔迪森所述已退化成科技水平很低的部落，例外书中人物阿雷文（{{lang|en|Arevin}}）就从未见过书籍<ref name="Jordison 2012">{{cite news | last = Jordison | first = Sam | title = Back to the Hugos: Dreamsnake by Vonda N McIntyre | url = https://www.theguardian.com/books/2012/apr/16/back-to-the-hugos-vonda-n-mcintyre | access-date = 2021-03-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191109002809/https://www.theguardian.com/books/2012/apr/16/back-to-the-hugos-vonda-n-mcintyre | work = The Guardian | date = 2012-04-16 | archive-date = 2019-11-09 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="Cordle-2017">{{cite book | first = Daniel | last = Cordle | title = Late Cold War Literature and Culture: The Nuclear 1980s | access-date = 2021-03-23 | url = https://books.google.co.jp/books?id=bMJCDgAAQBAJ&redir_esc=y | year = 2017 | publisher = Palgrave Macmillan UK | isbn = 978-1-137-51308-3 | page = 107–108, 177}}</ref>。只有名为“中心”的城市拥有先进科技且能与其他行星接触<ref name="Holland" /><ref name="Paulsen-1984" />{{rp|104}}<ref name="McIntyre-1978">{{cite book | first = Vonda N. | last = McIntyre | year = 1978 | title = Dreamsnake | publisher = Houghton Mifflin | isbn = 978-0-395-26470-6}}</ref>{{rp|36–37}}，但城内等级森严且不准外来者进入<ref name="Wolmark-1988">{{cite journal | last = Wolmark | first = Jenny | title = Alternative futures? Science fiction and feminism | journal = Cultural Studies | volume = 2 | issue = 1 | year = 1988 | pages = 48–56 | issn = 0950-2386 | doi = 10.1080/09502388800490021}}</ref>{{rp|54}}。麦金泰尔的第一部小说《流亡等待》（{{lang|en|''The Exile Waiting''}}，1975年）也以“中心”为背景<ref name="ESF" /><ref name="Lefanu-1989" />。《梦蛇》的主角名叫“舞蛇”（{{lang|en|Snake}}）<ref name="Chinese">{{cite book | title = 梦蛇 | publisher = 天地出版社 | isbn = 9787545537307 | author = 冯达·N.麦金泰尔 | work = 狮鹫文学 | date = 2008-09-01 | translator = 齐如君}}</ref>，能用蛇毒治病。她带着三条[[基因工程|转基因]]蛇出行，分别是名叫“沙”的[[響尾蛇|響尾蛇]]，名叫“雾”的[[眼镜蛇|眼镜蛇]]，以及名叫“草”的“梦蛇”，梦蛇来自外星球，能让垂死的病人进入美梦来缓解病痛<ref name="Sandomir" /><ref name="Lacey-2018">{{cite encyclopedia | editor-first1 = Gerry | editor-last1 = Canavan | editor-first2 = Eric Carl | editor-last2 = Link | title = Science Fiction, Gender, and Sexuality in the New Wave | first = Lauren J. | last = Lacey | encyclopedia = The Cambridge History of Science Fiction | access-date = 2021-03-23 | url = https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=F4B-DwAAQBAJ&pg=PT500&redir_esc=y&hl=zh-CN&sourceid=cndr | pages = 375–376 | year = 2018 | publisher = Cambridge University Press | isbn = 978-1-316-73301-1}}</ref>。

== 情节大纲 ==
小说以舞蛇到游牧部落治疗身患癌症的男童史达宾（{{lang|en|Stavin}}）开始<ref name="Chinese" />，她让梦蛇“草”送患者入眠，眼镜蛇“雾”用毒腺制作解毒剂<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|1–7}}。牧民阿雷文帮舞蛇控制当晚一直在抽搐的眼镜蛇，部落其他人对蛇非常害怕。早上舞蛇来到史达宾身边，发现孩子的父母生怕蛇会伤人，已经把“草”打成重伤，她也回天乏术。舞蛇虽然愤怒，但还是让“雾”去咬史达宾来注入解毒剂。部落首领向舞蛇致歉，阿雷文请她留在部落，但舞蛇表示她需要梦蛇才能治病，必须回家另找一条。她担心其他治疗师会把她驱逐并将蛇抢走，阿雷文在她离开时邀请舞蛇今后回来作客。<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|7–22}}{{refn|group="注"|《雾草沙》以舞蛇离开牧师部落营地结束<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|7–22}}。}}

舞蛇在绿洲歇脚，梅里迪斯（{{lang|en|Merideth}}）的女伴杰西（{{lang|en|Jesse}}）跌落马背受伤，把舞蛇带到营地要求救治，把治疗师的行李留在绿洲。舞蛇发现杰西因脊椎骨折瘫痪，她根本没法儿治。<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|23–30}}杰西来自“中心”，梅里迪斯和同伴亚历克斯（{{lang|en|Alex}}）劝她回去，希望外星人能治好她<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|33–38}}。舞蛇在营地附近转悠，发现杰西的马已死，明白这里的放射污染很强，杰西停留时间太长，辐射中毒足以致命。舞蛇表示可以用“雾”咬杰西缓解痛苦，杰西同意，梅里迪斯和亚历克斯向她告别。杰西临死前告诉舞蛇，能这样解脱她很感激，请舞蛇去找她的家人，或许他们能帮忙从外星球找来梦蛇。<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|45–54}}

舞蛇回到绿洲后发现行李被盗，日记也没了，同在绿洲扎营的商队领袖格鲁姆（{{lang|en|Grum}}）宣称这是“疯子”干的<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|64–69}}。游牧部落的阿雷文决定去找舞蛇<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|60–62}}。舞蛇穿过西部沙漠抵达“山腰”城，市长之子加布里埃尔（{{lang|en|Gabriel}}）请她救治市长<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|84–88}}。舞蛇邀请加布里埃尔和她上床，得知他曾因“生物控制”技能没学到家令朋友怀孕，进而导致他和父亲关系紧张<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|111–116}}。舞蛇告诉加布里埃尔继续学习，遵从心中打算离开“山腰”后另找老师<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|111–116}}。

舞蛇在检查马匹时遇到面部严重烧伤的梅丽莎（{{lang|en|Melissa}}），后者帮马厩主喂马<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|104–107, 134–135}}。梅丽莎因面部疤痕自卑，觉得山腰其他人都比她好看<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|142–143, 149–157}}。舞蛇前往市长家时遇人偷袭，估计是“疯子”所为<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|126–130}}。她发现梅丽莎受到马厩主的肉体和性虐待后告诉市长，市长同意放梅丽莎自由。舞蛇离开山腰前往中心，已是她养女的梅丽莎一起上路。<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|142–143, 149–157}}舞蛇告诉养女，梦蛇非常罕见，而且人们至今不知如何让它们繁殖<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|158–159}}。阿雷文抵达舞蛇位于山腰北面的住所，得知她不在后南下寻找<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|164–171}}。山腰的人误以为是阿雷文之前偷袭舞蛇而将他逮捕，但发现只是误会后释放<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|216–218}}。

舞蛇与梅丽莎经东部沙漠抵达中心，但就像其他治疗师一样被拒之门外<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|179–185}}。返回山区后两人又遇到疯子袭击，原来他已对梦蛇的毒液上瘾，得知舞蛇的梦蛇已死后精神崩溃<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|199–201}}。舞蛇迫使疯子带路前往“北方”（{{lang|en|North}}）统领的社区，原来“北方”拥有很多舞蛇，有时为奖励追随者会用舞蛇咬他们<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|205–207}}。这帮人在“破碎的圆顶”生活，昔日文明所在如今只剩下残破遗迹<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|220–225}}。北方非常憎恨治疗师，把舞蛇扔进满是梦蛇的寒冷大坑<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|234–237}}。舞蛇根据眼前所见明白梦蛇要在寒冷环境才会性成熟，并且不像地球上那样雌雄交配，需三条梦蛇才能繁殖<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|254–255}}。舞蛇已对蛇毒免疫，所以在大堆梦蛇中活下来并爬出深坑。北方的部下已陷入蛇毒产生的美梦，舞蛇借机找到同样昏迷的梅丽莎，带着满袋梦蛇一起逃走。她离开破碎的圆顶后遇到阿雷文，后者帮忙救醒梅丽莎。<ref name="McIntyre-1978" />{{rp|267–275}}

== 主题与结构 ==
《梦蛇》是科幻文学[[第二波女性主義|第二波女权主义]]的典范之作，20世纪60到70年代大量女作家投入创作前，科幻文学以强调阳刚气质的男子历险为主，但第二波女权主义已经颠覆这种传统<ref name="Kilgore-2000">{{cite journal | last = Kilgore | first = De Witt Douglas | title = Vonda N. McIntyre's Parodic Astrofuturism | journal = Science Fiction Studies | date = 2000-07 | volume = 27 | issue = 2 | pages = 256–277 | jstor = 4240879}}</ref>{{rp|260–261}}<ref name="Wolmark-1988" />{{rp|51}}。麦金泰尔立足末日浩劫后的世界，站在女权立场探讨各种社会结构和性别固定思维<ref name="Wolmark-1988" />{{rp|54}}。女人的[[性欲|欲望]]在她笔下地位突出，以舞蛇到访各社区的所见所闻和行为呈现[[性别角色|性别关系]]<ref name="Wolmark-1994">{{cite book | first = Jenny | last = Wolmark | title = Aliens and Others: Science Fiction, Feminism and Postmodernism | url = https://books.google.co.jp/books?id=GyMtyOLsQW4C&redir_esc=y | year = 1994 | publisher = University of Iowa Press | isbn = 978-0-87745-447-2 | access-date = 2021-03-23}}</ref>{{rp|63–65}}。女人占据众多领导位置，作者后来的《星际战士》（{{lang|en|''Starfarers''}}）系列作品也是如此<ref name="Kilgore-2000" />{{rp|266}}。传统的[[英雄旅程|英雄旅程]]在此改写，《梦蛇》的核心人物是女子<ref name="Wolmark-1994" />{{rp|65}}，她面临的挑战不需要武力对抗，而需治疗和照顾<ref name="Williams-2002">{{cite encyclopedia | editor-first1 = Fiona | editor-last1 = Kelleghan | encyclopedia = Classics of Science Fiction and Fantasy Literature | last = Williams | first = Donna Glee | title = Dreamsnake | year = 2002 | publisher = Salem Press | isbn = 978-1-58765-050-5 | pages = 152–154}}</ref>。科幻小说中女爱人追求或等待男英雄的传统模式在此逆转，变成阿雷文追随舞蛇，而且女主角不需要他去拯救<ref name="Wendell-1982">{{cite encyclopedia | last = Wendell | first = Carolyn | title = Responsible Rebellion in Vonda McIntyre's ''Fireflood'', ''Dreamsnake'', and ''Exile Waiting'' | encyclopedia = Critical encounters II : Writers and Themes in Science Fiction | editor-first = Tom | editor-last = Staicar | publisher = F. Ungar | year = 1982 | isbn = 978-0-8044-2837-8 | pages = 125–144}}</ref>{{rp|143}}。文中梅里迪斯始终性别不明<ref name="Kilgore-2000" />{{rp|275}}，作者为颠覆性别期望完全不用性别代词<ref name="Le Guin-2016">{{cite book | last = Le Guin | first = Ursula | chapter = The Wild Winds of Possibility: Vonda N. McIntyre's ''Dreamsnake'' | title = Words Are My Matter | publisher = Small Beer Press | year = 2016 | isbn = 978-1-61873-134-0}}</ref>{{rp|139–142}}，以此营造“女权构想”，表明人的性格与能力比性别重要<ref name="Kilgore-2000" />{{rp|275}}。人物出场时通常先透露职业，后来才在不经意间揭示她们是女人，潜移默化地扭转读者期望<ref name="Williams-2002" /><ref name="Cordle-2017" /><ref name="Wendell-1982" />{{rp|126}}。

学者英格丽丝·保尔森（{{lang|en|Inge-Lise Paulsen}}）认为书中对治疗和整体化的探讨也涉及女权主题。舞蛇是职业治疗师，从表面上看似乎符合女子养育、护理的传统形象。但情节展开后读者不难发现，舞蛇是因为接受这方面训练而当治疗师，属于道德选择，与她是女人无关。书尾她和阿雷文、梅丽莎似乎组成家庭，但这不是她“身为女人的终极成就”。<ref name="Paulsen-1984" />{{rp|104–105}}小说结束时她最重要的成就是发现梦蛇如何繁殖。爱情不足以维系关系，阿雷文必须学会信任舞蛇的实力，而不是老想着要保护她。小说开头游牧部落的乌托邦社会结构体现互相尊重。<ref name="Paulsen-1984" />{{rp|104–105}}游牧民族尊重个人，相互帮助，与为自我保护与世界隔离的城镇人口截然相反<ref name="Paulsen-1984" />{{rp|104–106}}。保尔森认为书中城镇人口带有典型的[[父權|父權]]制文化倾向，作者描绘整体道德需求和对社会各方面联系的理解，与勒瑰恩的作品和[[多丽丝·莱辛|多丽丝·莱辛]]《[[阿尔戈斯老人星|阿尔戈斯老人星]]》（{{lang|en|''Canopus in Argos''}}）系列异曲同工<ref name="Paulsen-1984" />{{rp|105–106}}。
[[File:Caduceus2.svg|thumb]]

《梦蛇》的行文传达复杂和多重含义，激发读者深入思考<ref name="Wood-1990" />{{rp|63}}。主人翁叫舞蛇、结合用来治病的蛇让人想到宗教和神话影像。[[商神杖|商神杖]]或[[双蛇绕杖|双蛇绕杖]]是现代医学的标志，[[希腊神话|希腊神话]]中商神杖代表[[赫耳墨斯|赫耳墨斯]]，拥有各种神圣知识。<ref>{{cite journal | first = Anne Hudson | last = Jones | title = The Healer-Patient/Family Relationship in Vonda N. McIntyre's "Of Mist, and Grass, and Sand" | journal = Perspectives in Biology and Medicine | volume = 26 | issue = 2 | date = Winter 1983 | doi = 10.1353/pbm.1983.0037 | pmid = 6844117 | pages = 277–279}}</ref>蛇还有死亡、复兴等[[蛇_(象徵)|其他象征意义]]，在小说中以各种角色或形式反复出现<ref name="Wood-1990" />{{rp|65–66}}<ref name=Westfahl-2005>{{cite book | first = Gary | last = Westfahl | title = The Greenwood Encyclopedia of Science Fiction and Fantasy: Themes, Works, and Wonders | access-date = 2021-03-23 | page = 370 | year = 2005 | publisher = Greenwood Publishing Group | isbn = 978-0-313-32952-4 | url = https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=3JXnz9x9sO4C&pg=PA730&redir_esc=y&hl=zh-CN&sourceid=cndr#v=onepage&q&f=false}}</ref>。蛇象征毒药和治疗，书中的舞蛇带蛇治病，让人想到手持[[阿斯克勒庇俄斯之杖|蛇杖]]的罗马神话医神[[阿斯克勒庇俄斯|阿斯克勒庇俄斯]]<ref name="Wood-1990" />{{rp|65–66}}。梦蛇“草”同样包含双重含义，既是治疗师的有力工具，又令沙漠牧民恐惧不已<ref name="Wood-1990" />{{rp|64–65}}。舞蛇用蛇治疗与[[創世記|圣经的创世纪神话]]呼应，但又将神话反转变成女人控制蛇<ref name="Wolmark-1994" />{{rp|64–65}}。书中拥有尖端科技的城市“中心”与其他社会隔绝，以此探索“中心与边缘、内与外、自我与他人”的关系，这也是麦金泰尔小说《流亡等待》和《[[超光速|超光速]]》的主题<ref name="Wolmark-1994" />{{rp|57}}。中心的社会秩序非常严格，相比之下，中心以外、包括社会边缘都会发生社会变革，“中心”空有其名，对书中绝大多数人物和读者根本无关紧要<ref name="Wolmark-1994" />{{rp|57–58}}。

《梦蛇》与麦金泰尔大部分作品一样探讨自由和监禁的影响。她笔下许多角色都力图摆脱某种束缚，如自我强加的心理限制，体能或外表缺陷引起的挑战，其他人的压迫等<ref name="Wendell-1982" />{{rp|127–128}}。舞蛇遇到两名为山腰市长工作的奴隶，市长已在全城禁止奴隶制还他们自由。其中一人脚后跟附有代表奴隶身份的标志环，舞蛇告诉她可以帮忙去掉，但有可能导致瘸脚，她听后依然喜出望外。另一人自由后出于感激自认有义务落实市长的所有构想。<ref name="Wendell-1982" />{{rp|127–129}}梅丽莎因烧伤毁容，当地社会根据外表裁定人的价值，所以她隐藏起来，对社会而言几乎不存在<ref name="Wendell-1982" />{{rp|132–133}}。其他角色同样身处束缚：“北方”患有无药可治的[[巨人症|巨人症]]，导致一直身陷精神病型愤怒；“疯子”对蛇毒上瘾无法自拔；加布里埃尔对未能控制生育感到羞愧；阿雷文为家庭责任所困<ref name="Wendell-1982" />{{rp|141–143}}。

文化规范间互动的主题在《梦蛇》反复出现，有时还具双重含义，如舞蛇与阿雷文探讨“朋友”时，阿雷文更加重视，山区居民还用这个词来表示愿与他人发生性关系<ref name="Wood-1990" />{{rp|69–70}}。阿雷文起初不愿把姓名告诉舞蛇，他对“朋友”的解释说明游牧民族对外来人士疑虑根深蒂固，离开部落后，他从文化角度向舞蛇解释为什么牧民会杀死梦蛇“草”<ref name="Wood-1990" />{{rp|69–70}}。文化偏见导致治疗师难以理解梦蛇的生理机能。对地球生物的了解导致他们误以为梦蛇也是雌雄两条配对繁殖，只有舞蛇因对蛇毒免疫才发现需要三条才能繁殖的真相<ref name="Wood-1990" />{{rp|68–70}}。作者以此传达接受不同能带来成长和变革的理念<ref name="Wolmark-1994" />{{rp|65–66}}。

== 人物 ==
评论家特别关注《梦蛇》的强势女主角<ref name="SCS 1979">{{cite news | title = Dreamsnake, by Vonda McIntyre | work = Santa Cruz Sentinel | page = 23 | date = 1979-07-22}}</ref><ref name="Estes 1978">{{cite news | last = Estes | first = Sally | title = Fear the Dragon No Longer | work = The Park City Daily News | page = 34 | date = 1978-09-17}}</ref>。作者借舞蛇的核心地位把性别当成核心主题<ref name="Wolmark-1994" />{{rp|64–65}}，颠覆性别思维定势<ref name="Paulsen-1984" /><ref name="Wolmark-1994" />{{rp|64–65}}。与麦金泰尔许多作品的主人翁一样，舞蛇也是自信的女人，扮演传统上属于男人的角色，只不过她是治疗师而不是典型的男英雄<ref name="Wendell-1982" />{{rp|125–126}}<ref name="Cordle-2017" />。《梦蛇》大部分男角色形象趋于负面，如山腰城市长、虐待梅丽莎的马厩主、“北方”等；“温柔而执着”的阿雷文在书中出场极少，大部分时间只是背景人物<ref name="Wendell-1982" />{{rp|126}}。

[[奥森·斯科特·卡德|奥森·斯科特·卡德]]认为舞蛇完全做到独立自主乃至自给自足：遇到的问题她自己解决，在结尾也不像传统小说那样等待男人拯救。舞蛇和[[獨行俠|獨行俠]]非常相似，以“爱和理解”改善人民生活：她为格鲁姆的商队免疫、救出梅丽莎，帮加布里埃尔克服执念并鼓励他成长和独立。<ref name="Card 1978">{{cite journal | last = Card | first = Orson Scott | title = Dreamsnake | journal = Science Fiction Review | date = 1978-11-10 | volume = 7 | issue = 4 | url = https://archive.org/details/Science_Fiction_Review_27v07n04_1978-09-10/page/n31/mode/2up?q=dreamsnake | pages = 32–33 | access-date = 2021-03-23}}</ref>学者莎拉·勒范努（{{lang|en|Sarah LeFanu}}）觉得舞蛇就像《流亡等待》排除万难竭力逃出“中心”的主人翁米沙（{{lang|en|Mischa}}），只不过“年纪更大、更有智慧”。在勒范努看来，舞蛇“勇敢、忠诚、聪明”，为人善良且有强烈的正义感。<ref name="Lefanu-1989" />

学者卡罗琳·温德尔（{{lang|en|Carolyn Wendell}}）指出，舞蛇与书中大部分人物相比更能自主决择。自由赋予她更大的责任，令她有能力解放加布里埃尔和梅丽莎等人。<ref name="Wendell-1982" />{{rp|143–144}}发生性关系后，舞蛇与传统科幻小说中的女角色相比更能保留自我<ref name="Cordle-2017" />。勒范努认为作者在书中描写女主角发生性关系，结合贯穿全书始终的性别政治，意在表达《舞蛇》的世界里“女人就可以代表全人类” <ref name="Lefanu-1989" />。还有作家认为，舞蛇堪称女权思想下的[[巫術|女巫]]原型，父权社会对她们避之唯恐不及，在此摇身一变成为女人权力的象征<ref>{{cite book | first = Angelika | last = Bammer | title = Partial Visions | year = 2012 | publisher = Routledge | access-date = 2021-03-23 | isbn = 978-1-134-98010-9 | pages = 85–86 | url = https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=ih36XTeHkZEC&pg=PA86&redir_esc=y&hl=zh-CN&sourceid=cndr#v=onepage&q&f=false}}</ref>。

== 评价和影响 ==
《梦蛇》获1978年[[星雲獎最佳長篇小說獎|星雲獎最佳長篇小說獎]]<ref>{{cite web | title = Keith Stokes, Vonda N. McIntyre honored with SFWA Service Award | archive-date = 2021-01-26 | dead-url = no | access-date = 2021-03-23 | date = 2010-03-11 | url = https://www.sfwa.org/2010/03/11/keith-stokes-vonda-n-mcintyre-honored-with-sfwa-service-award/ | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210126134916/https://www.sfwa.org/2010/03/11/keith-stokes-vonda-n-mcintyre-honored-with-sfwa-service-award/ | publisher = SWFA }}</ref><ref name="Lacey-2018" />、1979年[[雨果獎最佳長篇小說|雨果獎最佳長篇小說]]<ref name="Lacey-2018" /><ref>{{cite web | title = 1979 Hugo Awards | access-date = 2021-03-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210226020836/http://www.thehugoawards.org/hugo-history/1979-hugo-awards/ | dead-url = no | url = http://www.thehugoawards.org/hugo-history/1979-hugo-awards/ | work = The Hugo Awards | archive-date = 2021-02-26 }}</ref>和[[軌跡獎最佳長篇小說|轨迹奖最佳长篇小说]]<ref name="Lacey-2018" /><ref>{{cite web | title = 1979 Locus Awards | url = http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Locus1979.html | work = Locus Magazine | year = 1979 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150913102315/http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Locus1979.html | archive-date = 2015-09-13 | access-date = 2015-09-13 | dead-url = yes }}</ref>；还赢得西北太平洋书商奖肯定<ref>{{cite book | editor-first = Jonathan | editor-last = Strahan | chapter = Little Sisters – Vonda N. McIntyre | title = The Best Science Fiction and Fantasy of the Year, Volume Ten | access-date = 2021-03-23 | page = 349 | isbn = 978-1-84997-932-0 | url = https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=VVAEDAAAQBAJ&pg=PT349&redir_esc=y&hl=zh-CN&sourceid=cndr#v=onepage&q&f=false | year = 2016 | publisher = Solaris}}</ref>和1979年[[迪特玛奖|迪特玛奖]]国际小说奖提名<ref>{{cite web | title = 1979 Ditmar Awards | url = http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Ditmar1979.html | work = Locus Magazine | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150913104304/http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Ditmar1979.html | access-date = 2015-09-13 | dead-url = yes | archive-date = 2015-09-13 }}</ref>。1995年，《梦蛇》获詹姆斯·提普奇纪念奖提名<ref>{{cite web | title = 1995 Retrospective Honor List | archive-date = 2020-11-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201128074451/https://otherwiseaward.org/award/1995-retrospective-award/1995-retrospective-honor-list | url = https://otherwiseaward.org/award/1995-retrospective-award/1995-retrospective-honor-list | dead-url = no | website = James Tiptree, Jr. Award | access-date = 2021-03-23 }}</ref>。1974年，麦金泰尔因《雾草沙》首获[[星云奖|星云奖]]（[[星云奖最佳短篇小说|最佳短篇小说]]）<ref name="Ashley-2007" /><ref name="Loc74" />，并获[[雨果奖最佳短篇小说|雨果奖最佳短篇小说]]<ref name="Hugo74">{{cite web | url = http://www.thehugoawards.org/hugo-history/1974-hugo-awards/ | title = 1974 Hugo Awards | publisher = World Science Fiction Society | access-date = 2021-03-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210304214500/http://www.thehugoawards.org/hugo-history/1974-hugo-awards/ | archive-date = 2021-03-04 | dead-url = no }}</ref>及[[轨迹奖最佳短篇小说|轨迹奖最佳短篇小说]]提名<ref>{{cite web | title = 1974 Locus Awards | archive-date = 2015-09-14 | dead-url = yes | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150914162757/http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Locus1974.html | access-date = 2015-09-14 | url = http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Locus1974.html | website = Locus Magazine }}</ref>。1980年，小说[[平裝書|平裝書]]获[[美国图书奖|美国图书奖]]提名<ref name="Tymn-1981">{{cite book | last = Tymn | first = Marshall B. | url = https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=sDFaAAAAMAAJ&redir_esc=y&hl=zh-CN&sourceid=cndr | title = The Science fiction reference book | publisher = Starmont House | year = 1981 | isbn = 978-0-916732-49-3 | access-date = 2021-03-23}}</ref>{{rp|201–203}}{{refn|group="注"|美国图书奖把[[精裝書|精裝書]]和[[平裝書|平裝書]]分开处理，《梦蛇》的平装书1979年首发，所以有资格角逐1980年奖项，1978年出版的是精装书<ref name="Tymn-1981" />{{rp|201–203}}。}}。女作家在推想文学领域一度趋于边缘化，但20世纪70年代众多女作家以女权主义推想小说脱颖而出，《梦蛇》便是其中的重要作品。除麦金泰尔外，勒瑰恩、[[凯特·威廉|凯特·威廉]]（{{lang|en|Kate Wilhelm}}）和[[小詹姆斯·提普奇|小詹姆斯·提普奇]]均对此贡献很大。<ref>{{cite book | first = Carlen | last = Lavigne | title = Cyberpunk Women, Feminism and Science Fiction: A Critical Study | pages = 24–28 | year = 2013 | publisher = McFarland | access-date = 2012-03-23 | url = https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=5ER26ZJkc30C&redir_esc=y&hl=zh-CN&sourceid=cndr | isbn = 978-1-4766-0178-6}}</ref>

众多评论称赞作者文笔。《圣塔克鲁斯哨兵报》（''{{lang|en|Santa Cruz Sentinel}}''）赞扬小说情节“着实令人着迷”<ref name="SCS 1979" />，[[美國圖書館協會|美國圖書館協會]]的萨莉·埃斯蒂斯（{{lang|en|Sally Estes}}）也称“扣人心弦”<ref name="Estes 1978" />，《辛辛那提问询报》（''{{lang|en|Cincinnati Enquirer}}''）宣称《梦蛇》在1978年所有小说中无论情感还是诗意表现都名列前茅<ref>{{cite news | last = Waite | first = Dennis | title = Talking of Time Warps | work = The Cincinnati Enquirer | page = 119 | date = 1978-08-06}}</ref>。勒瑰恩赞扬小说“如山上溪流般迅速、干净、清晰、美丽，令人兴奋不已”<ref name="Le Guin 1978" />。她还在2011年撰文更进一步：“《梦蛇》文笔清晰、节奏明快，简短且情绪饱满的景观桥段直接把读者带到半熟悉、半陌生的沙漠世界，人物情感状态、情绪和情感变化的描写详尽、细致”<ref name="Le Guin-2016" />。科幻学者马歇尔·泰姆（{{lang|en|Marshall Tymn}}）1981年表示，《梦蛇》主人翁的历险富含诗意、值得细致探讨而且倍感真实，这正是小说成功的重要原因，在众多雨果奖和星云奖获奖作品中可谓历久弥新<ref name="Tymn-1981" />{{rp|372}}。2012年《[[衛報|衛報]]》刊文宣称《梦蛇》“充满挑战，令人坐立不安”，称赞麦金泰尔以精细的笔触描绘虚构世界<ref name="Jordison 2012" />。

小说的主题、符号和遣词用句同样引起关注。学者黛安·伍德（{{lang|en|Diane Wood}}）声称《梦蛇》体现“科幻文学以语言和文化规范实验产生美感的潜力”<ref name="Wood-1990" />{{rp|63}}。她称赞作者弘扬跨文化交流主题，写作风格与“生动人物”令作品在倡导“更加充分的同情与理解”时更具说服力，小说“极具质感”，读来心旷神怡<ref name="Wood-1990" />{{rp|71–72}}。学者加里·韦斯法尔（{{lang|en|Gary Wesfahl}}）把麦金泰尔笔下的蛇与其他推想小说相比，声称《梦蛇》在描绘虚构人蛇关系领域达到领先地位<ref name=Westfahl-2005 />。卡德强调舞蛇的自给自足，赞扬作者以浅显情节创造“邪恶而美丽的世界”，人物塑造丰满生动<ref name="Card 1978" />。

部分评论从篇幅和结构入手，从多个角度对比《梦蛇》和《雾草沙》。《[[夏洛特观察家报|夏洛特观察家报]]》（''{{lang|en|Charlotte Observer}}''）发文批评《梦蛇》绝大部分篇幅没有实质内容，证明优秀的短篇小说不一定适合扩充成长篇<ref>{{cite news | last = Lloyd | first = David | title = Another Best Seller? | work = The Charlotte Observer | page = 52 | date = 1978-06-02}}</ref>；埃斯蒂斯也觉得长篇与短篇原作相比“少了某些微妙之处”<ref name="Estes 1978" />。还有评论认为阿雷文出场情节太少，根本没必要保留。温德尔1982年撰文表示，阿雷文出场也是颠覆传统，看不惯的评论员其实是不习惯女主人翁自行解决困难。<ref name="Wendell-1982" />{{rp|143}}[[布莱恩·斯坦伯福德|布莱恩·斯坦伯福德]]（{{lang|en|Brian Stableford}}）觉得《梦蛇》的情节过于简单，但这不影响成效。在他看来，本文“很有想法和诚意”，非常值得一看。<ref name="Stableford 1979">{{cite journal | last = Stableford | first = Brian | title = Dreamsnake | journal = Foundation | date = 1975-05 | issue = 16 | pages = 70–71}}</ref>卡德认为《雾草沙》已经算得上“完美抛光的宝石”，一度觉得扩充可能得不偿失。他批评长篇有些桥段过于感伤，如描写梅丽莎的部分，还有些情节拖得太长。但整体而言，他觉得小说意犹未尽。<ref name="Card 1978" />

